          <Comment Type="public">The variant is observed as homozygous in at least two unrelated individuals/adults in the gnomAD v4.1.0 dataset. Predicted Consequence/Location: Missense variant In silico tool predictions suggest damaging effect of the variant on gene or gene product [REVEL: 0.84 (&gt;=0.6, sensitivity 0.68 and specificity 0.92)]. The variant has been reportedas being highly correlated with development of neural tube defects in thegeneralpopulation. (PMID: 32536242, ClinVar ID: VCV000003520). Therefore, this variant is classified as Risk allele according to the recommendation of ACMG/AMP guideline.</Comment>
