        <ClinVarAccession Accession="SCV007601567" DateUpdated="2026-06-27" DateCreated="2026-06-27" Type="SCV" Version="1" SubmitterName="Department of Clinical Medical Laboratory, The Second Hospital of Lanzhou University" OrgID="510603" OrganizationCategory="laboratory"/>
        <RecordStatus>current</RecordStatus>
        <Classification DateLastEvaluated="2026-06-08">
          <ReviewStatus>no assertion criteria provided</ReviewStatus>
          <GermlineClassification>Likely risk allele</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment Type="public">Case-control association study of MTHFR C677T (c.665C&gt;T, rs1801133) and ischemic stroke in a Chinese Han population. Study included 121 ischemic stroke patients (cases) and 121 healthy controls. Genotyping was performed using PCR-RFLP. The T allele frequency was significantly higher in cases (62.40%) than in controls (51.65%). Allelic association: OR=1.55, 95% CI=1.08-2.23, P=0.017 (chi-square test). Genotype distribution in cases: CC=24, CT=43, TT=54; in controls: CC=29, CT=59, TT=33. The control group was in Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium (P=0.794). These results suggest that the MTHFR C677T polymorphism is a risk factor for ischemic stroke.</Comment>
        </Classification>
